<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2007-11-04T20:04:18-07:00</updated>
<published>2007-11-04T20:04:18-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3666&amp;p=27931#p27931</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3666&amp;p=27931#p27931"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Status Bar - SMB3/MMSILL/MMAINL/SMW(NESPirate) Help]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3666&amp;p=27931#p27931"><![CDATA[
Background information: <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parallax_scrolling" class="postlink">Parallax scrolling on Wikipedia</a><br /><br />Super Mario Bros. 3 uses the 32x60 cell ("horizontal mirroring") playfield mode, splitting it into a 54-cell-tall playfield and a 6-cell-tall status bar. It sets the MMC3 to trigger an IRQ near the bottom of the screen. The IRQ handler sets the VRAM address registers to the top of the status bar, and the PPU starts drawing from there.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Nov 04, 2007 8:04 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
